# SLEIGH spec for the NMOS 6510 (6502 + undocumented opcodes), as used on the
# Commodore 64. The stock 6502 legal-instruction spec is pulled in verbatim, then
# the illegal opcodes are layered on. 6502.slaspec is NOT committed here (it is
# Ghidra's, Apache-2.0); build.py copies it beside this file from either
# $GHIDRA_INSTALL_DIR or a pypcode install before invoking the SLEIGH compiler.
@include "6502.slaspec"
@include "6510_illegal.sinc"
